                "title": "Efficient alignment of illumina-like high-throughput sequencing reads with the GEnomic multi-tool (GEM) mapper", 
                "abstract": "© 2015 by John Wiley & Sons, Inc. Modern Illumina-like high-throughput sequencing machines allow the cheap decoding of great amounts of DNA. The GEnomic Multi-tool (GEM) mapper is one of the fastest and most sensitive methods known to date to align such data to a known genomic reference. This unit explains how to use it effectively.", 
